http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/AP-inks-MoUs-for-Rs.4.78-lakh-crore/article13995967.ece

Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu on Tuesday announced that they would hold Davos-type interface with stakeholders regularly to extend the benefits of development to the common man after signing pacts worth Rs. 4.78 lakh crore with investors from India and the Middle East, the United States, China and other countries.The pacts were signed during the three-day CII Partnership Summit titled ‘Sunrise Andhra Pradesh Investment Meet’ concluded at APIIC Harbour Park. As many as 328 MoUs signed has a potential to create employment for nearly ten lakh people, Mr. Naidu said Major investment proposals include Essel and ZEE Goup establishing smart industrial parks, including LNG terminal, involving an investment of about $ nine billion indirectly by encouraging various Chinese and Indian companies to set up base in the park. The MoU also covers an investment of $ two billion directly into setting up of a state-of-the-art manufacturing hub for renewal energy equipment manufacturing. Agreements for setting up a Rs.5,000 crore naval facility at Rambilli, near here, by Anil Ambani’s ADA Group and for a Rs.38,000-crore expansion project by RINL were also signed.Addressing the valedictory attended by several dignitaries, including Governor E.S.L. Narasimhan, Union Minister for Fertilizers and Chemicals, Ananth Kumar, Union Civil Aviation Minister, P. Ashok Gajapathi Raju and Union Minister of State for Science and Technology, Y.S. Chowdary, Mr Naidu said they would hold Partnership Summit again next year in Visakhapatnam to ensure continuity and review progress of work on the projects.He also directed the Ministers and officials to hold review meetings regularly to ensure execution of various projects. He thanked the investors both from India and abroad for their confidence in investing in Vijayawada-Guntur Capital Region, Visakhapatnam, Tirupati and all other areas to ensure balanced development.Beating the worldwide economic slowdown, Andhra Pradesh, despite being a new state achieved a growth rate of 11 plus per cent with plans to raise it to 14 to 15 per cent in next few years convincing investors to look at opportunities in the State, Union Finance Minister, Arun Jaitley, had said during the inaugural address.